23/03/2004
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Several opposition parties in Republika Srpska (RS), led by the Union of Independent Social Democrats (SNSD), vowed to hold protests Tuesday (23 March) in Banja Luka. SNSD leader Milorad Dodik told reporters that up to 25,000 people are expected at the rallies, aimed at pushing for political change. The opposition is also threatening to initiate mass protests across RS unless early elections are held.
In other news, a ceremony was held Monday in Mostar, in advance of the 1 April handover of the airport there from SFOR personnel to BiH authorities. Officials stressed that the priority would be observing international standards. (OHR Sources, RTRS, Nezavisne novine, Oslobodjenje, Dnevni Avaz - 23/03/04)
